# Canonical Type Reuse

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/common/canonical-types.md](../../docs/agent/standards/common/canonical-types.md)
Skill: `.cursor/skills/canonical-type-reuse/SKILL.md`

## Types that MUST come from `src/api/src/core/`

| Type | Location | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `PaginatedResult<T>` | `src/core/types.ts` | All `findAll()` / `search()` returns |
| `PaginationParams` | `src/core/types.ts` | All list/search DTOs |
| `AppError` + subclasses | `src/core/error/` | All thrown errors |
| `AuditEntry` | `src/core/audit/` | All mutation audit records |
| `StorageUploadResult` | `src/core/storage/` | File upload responses |

## Types that MUST NOT be duplicated across domains

- `UserId` — always `string` (UUID) typed alias from `src/core/types.ts`
- `JobId`, `CompanyId`, `ApplicationId` — typed aliases, never raw `string`
- Pagination shape: always `{ data: T[]; meta: PaginationMeta }` — never custom pagination shapes

## Rules

- Before defining a new type, search `src/core/` and `docs/agent/standards/common/canonical-types.md` for an existing type.
- If a type is used in 2+ domains, it belongs in `src/core/`.
- Typed ID aliases prevent accidentally passing a `JobId` where a `CompanyId` is expected.
